FBIS4-36034 "drnes107_j_94027" FBIS-NES-94-107 Daily Report 2 Jun 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen South Announces Democratic Republic Government South Announces Democratic Republic Government EA0206163194 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 2 Jun 94 EA0206163194 Aden Democratic Republic of Yemen Radio Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 2 Jun 94 Arabic BFN ["Republican Decree No. 1" on the formation of the Democratic Republic of Yemen Council of Ministers issued in Aden on 1 June] [Text] In the name of God, the merciful and compassionate, Democratic Republic of Yemen [DRY], the chairman of the Presidential Council, having consulted the interim Constitution of the DRY and the decree of the Presidential Council No. 3 of 1994, charging brother Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas with the task of forming the government and following the approval of the Presidential Council, has decreed: Article 1: The Council of Ministers shall be formed in the following manner: ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Prime Minister and Finance Minister: |Haydar Abu-Bakr al-'Attas | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Deputy Prime Minister: |Muhammad Haydarah Masdus | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of |Muhsin Muhammad Bin Abu-Bakr Bin-Farid| |Planning and Development: | | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Deputy Prime Minister and Minister of |Salih Ubayd Ahmad | |Transport and Communications: | | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Deputy Prime Minister and Foreign Min-|'Abdallah 'Abd-al-Majid al-Asnaj | |ister: | | ------------------------------------------------------------------------------- |Defense Minister: |Staff Brigadier Adier Haytham Qasim T-| | |ahir | --------------------------------------------------------